{"questionId":"9084637","questionHtml":"<p>A proton and an alpha particle are accelerated by the same electric potential difference. The kinetic energy of the proton is <em>E</em> and its de Broglie wavelength is <em>λ</em>.&nbsp;What is the kinetic energy and the de&nbsp;Broglie wavelength of the alpha particle?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width:521px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:39px;\">\n<td style=\"width:46px;height:39px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:228.469px;height:39px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Kinetic energy of alpha particle</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:249.531px;height:39px;text-align:center;\"><strong>De Broglie wavelength of alpha particle</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:22px;\">\n<td style=\"width:46px;height:22px;\">&nbsp;A.</td>\n<td style=\"width:228.469px;height:22px;text-align:center;\"><em>E</em></td>\n<td style=\"width:249.531px;height:22px;text-align:center;\">less than&nbsp;<em>λ</em>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:22px;\">\n<td style=\"width:46px;height:22px;\">&nbsp;B.</td>\n<td style=\"width:228.469px;height:22px;text-align:center;\"><em>E</em></td>\n<td style=\"width:249.531px;height:22px;text-align:center;\">greater than&nbsp;<em>λ</em>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:20px;\">\n<td style=\"width:46px;height:20px;\">&nbsp;C.</td>\n<td style=\"width:228.469px;height:20px;text-align:center;\">greater than <em>E</em>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:249.531px;height:20px;text-align:center;\">less than&nbsp;<em>λ</em>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:23px;\">\n<td style=\"width:46px;height:23px;\">&nbsp;D.</td>\n<td style=\"width:228.469px;height:23px;text-align:center;\">greater than <em>E</em>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:249.531px;height:23px;text-align:center;\">greater than&nbsp;<em>λ</em>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9084637","referenceCode":"EXE.1A.HL.TZ0.28","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A proton and an alpha particle are accelerated by the same electric potential difference. The kinetic energy of the proton is E and its de Broglie wavelength is λ. What is the kine","paper":"1A","level":"HL","questionNumber":"28","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["E. Nuclear and quantum physics","E. Nuclear and quantum physics","E.2 Quantum physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}